{
  "title": "The Ideal Protocol",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2ec9cf732008c473",
      "text": "The ideal fediverse protocol would:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "239cc8f981302a6d",
      "text": " * Enable users to easily migrate from one instance to another"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "94ac3b44c8f72466",
      "text": " * Have cryptographic public key security for DMs or private group messages"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "fcb22ff0ef5f0c67",
      "text": " * Not tie the user's identity to a domain name, which makes migration and identity management hard"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ba749b33ebb64f88",
      "text": " * The user's identity should be based upon a private key"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "254abd97830678eb",
      "text": " * Nomadic identity should be possible. That is, a user should be able to register their identity on multiple instances, and those instances should automatically synchronize. If one instance goes down the user can just log in on another."
    }
  ],
